'''Fruit vines''' have many advantages. They can:
* be [[easy-to-grow useful plants]]
* often grow in a large pot, on a [[balcony]]
* grow up a makeshift trellis or balcony railing
* provide dappled shade, with a pleasant cooling effect in [[summer]] or in [[hot climates]]
* provide an easy supply of fruit for eating fresh, cooking, or preserving (e.g. with a [[solar food dryer]].

== Examples of fruit vines ==
* [[Passionfruit]]
* [[Grape]]
* [[Kiwifruit]] (known just as "kiwis" in some countries)

